Description: The Holy Family near a lake. Landscape with the Virgin holding the swaddled Christ Child as she sits on the ass, Joseph walking behind them at centre right, three cherubs among the three tall trees growing on the mound in left middle distance; copy in reverse after Herman van Swanevelt Etching
Curator's comments: This a copy in reverse, for the original etching by Swanevelt and comment see 1844,0425.15
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (6) (copy)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (monogram with date 1791)
